Checkpoint!

Well, I'm not quite sure what to make of this song...  Some people say this is the end, but if I'm being honest, I don't want to believe that.  I can't bring myself to believe that after I wrote about my relationship with my girlfriend over the past year on the vines video uploaded by this user.  I truly do love being with her, despite all of the hardships this relationship has brought.  

No, instead I choose to flow with the energetic and up-beat rhythm of this song.  While the path ahead may seem distorted in odd ways from mankind's desire for creating the world in their own twisted image, the occasional breaks form the metallic clattering and clangs in this song is a good reminder that while the world around you may seem like complete chaos, you can provide your own calm to your personal segment of this ever-raging storm.  

To make a long story short, if we face the challenges ahead with courage and determination, I'm sure we'll all end up okay.  This isn't the end, we can do this.

Checkpoint! Life has been tough for everyone in the last year, and for me, many of my problems with anxiety and motivation were worsened by the pandemic. Why is there so much chaos and hatred in the world? We're all humans, sitting on a big chunk of rock floating through space. For those of you who have been suffering silently this last year, have lost a loved one, or discovered you don't have as much control over your life as you thought you had, I stand with you. For those of you who are sick, mentally ill, lonely, or malnourished, I stand with you. And where do we stand? At the cusp of great change in the world. We can make it. We can save the planet and make it a better place to live for all. This big chunk of rock called earth? It's clay in our hands. We can mold it and shape it how we please. author: NSPBWii
text:
Checkpoint 4

I've been avoiding this one. There's only so many checkpoints that i can use, and i wanted to write something worthy in this checkpoint. Back in checkpoint 3, i was lying down in the murky swamp, watching the stars with some dragonflies. Life was pretty disappointing back then. I thought i couldn't trust nobody, that no one could ever understand or love me. Now here i am, Two and a half months later. And i have learned so many things.

First of all, i wrote a nasty blog post where i wrote everything that i hated about my family. I said so many mean things. Things that i believed for years. And although i felt bad for outing my issues with my family in a passive aggressive way, i don't regret that decision, because in the aftermath of that disastrous blog post, i could finally talk with my family, and that allowed me to let go of the pain that i carried for so many years. There were better alternatives, though, and i strongly recommend that you, the person reading this, consider talking with the people that don't make you feel right, before taking more extreme measures.

That being said, i've been being more assertive lately, because i realized that disagreeing with the people you love doesn't mean that you love them less. Putting your necessities first doesn't mean you don't appreciate them. And sometimes being honest is the best thing you can do. And yes, it will be uncomfortable. But it is worth the short-term pain.

And then i got cancelled. Yes. That's right. I made a prank on my exes where i texted them and treated them like we never broke up, so then i could take a snapshot of their reactions. It was a somewhat innocent prank, and i did it because so many people wanted to see that. But some friends, mostly women, didn't liked it at all. First of all, my exes called me immature for doing that. And then an acquaintance told me i was so mean for using my exes for attention. And some people that i considered close friends before took their side, even after i sincerely apologized for that. And they don't talk with me anymore. The most painful realization was that my best friend of more than 10 years would throw out our friendship without thinking twice. But i got out of there with valuable lessons: Sometimes you gotta think twice about what you say and what you do. Not because you might offend someone, but because you shouldn't do things that you are not entirely convinced to do. Don't succumb to peer pressure.

Then i had to accept what happened in my past relationships, and move on from them. It was a long and hard process where i had to admit that i made so many mistakes, and i can't really fix the past. There's only the now, and now they are not in my life, and that's ok. I can move on. Those relationships were NOT my peak. I can allow myself to have other relationships. There's no reason to stay in the past. And when i let go of the past... i started to feel peace again. I could finally love myself again, because i forgave myself from the mistakes of the past.

I procrastinated so hard during these months. I had to use these last weeks to save the semester. And even though it wasn't easy, and my procrastination showed up at the worst possible times, i still did it, proving that i'm capable of more than i thought before. I can overcome the challenges, and i'm a reliable person to take the wheel and drive my life wherever i want. My life was broken. But now i'm grateful for that, because i'm not blinded by expectations anymore. I can now use the pieces left to build a stronger life.

And now i'm in the mines. This is still a dark place, where the only light comes from the faraway exit of the tunnel and the lamps that other people left behind. But i'm no longer scared of this dark place. Sometimes, valuable things can be found in dark places like these. And now i can see i am surrounded by so many potentially valuable stones. Diamonds in the rough. Ores of gold and silver. So many pretty crystals. This is still a dark place in my life, and i gotta work to get value from this place. I can't carry the whole mine out, either. I gotta decide on what i want to work on. But i'm so grateful that i can finally see value in these hard times.

This is not the end. This is just the beginning. I've lived my life with so many lies in my mind. But now i can see that i'm not the hero of the story, and that's alright. I don't want to carry a heavy armor anymore. I don't want to survive. I don't want my life to be determined by how much people i have saved. I want to live my own life, doing what i love, and i love being creative. Writing, Drawing, having crazy ideas and acting on them. Doing art. If i want to live my crazy, twisted life, i gotta do what it takes to earn it. No more excuses. I gotta start mining the valuable ore and crystals of this dark mine.

This will get lost in the sea of checkpoints, but i want to thank you anyway for reading this wall of text. I love to write, and it would be nice if my ramblings could help someone out there. Who knows what's next in this journey? Life is so unpredictable, but that's part of the magic of it. We gotta keep going. Thanks. I see you in the next Checkpoint. This was a pretty good one for my favorite number.

Sincerely:
A 24 Year Old Mexican
22/Nov/2020

PS: I want to thank "Reyes Cedillo Joel Haidd" For their kind words in the last checkpoint. I readed them recently, but i really liked that you wanted to make a total stranger feel better. Thank you very much.

Study music theory and get some inspiration from famous video game composers, breaking down their songs to reveal what makes them so special. It's definitely an ambitious endeavor, but I know you can do it if you're willing to put the work in!
